<BODY>
<HEADLINE> German Ullrich Wins Tour de France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Jan Ullrich became the first German
to win the Tour de France cycling race on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Ullrich, who was second in 1996 and won two stages this year,
completed the 22-day classic in just over 100 hours to become at
23 years eight months the fourth youngest winner since 1947.
</P>
<P>
The German finished nine minutes nine seconds in front of
Richard Virenque of France, the biggest winning margin since 1984.
</P>
<P>
Virenque came in second and crowned king of the mountains for
the fourth Tour in succession.
</P>
<P>
Italian Marco Pantani was third for the second time in three
years.
</P>
<P>
German Erik Zabel took the points winner's green jersey for the
second consecutive year.
</P>
<P>
Nicola Minali of Italy won the last stage over 149.5 kilometers
from Disneyland in a sprint finish on the Champs Elysees. Minali
also won the fourth stage. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
