<HEADLINE> Cambodian FM Says Cambodia Wishes to Join ASEAN Soon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Cambodian Foreign Minister Ung
Huot today said Cambodia is willing to join the Association of
South East Asian Nations (ASEAN) as soon as possible despite a
delay in joining the regional group because of the domestic
conflict.
</P>
<P>
Cambodia welcomed the ASEAN to play a role in stablizing the
situation in Cambodia, said Ung Huot when he returned to Phnom
Penh from the 30th annual meeting of foreign ministers of the
ASEAN last Thursday and Friday and the ASEAN Regional Forum
security conference attended by major Asian and Western countries
on Sunday in Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
The minister, who went to Malaysia in the status of observer,
said the ASEAN had affirmed Cambodia's efforts to solve the
crisis, which began on July 5 with bloody clash between the troops
loyal to First Prime Minister Prince Norodom Ranariddh and Second
Prime Minister Hun Sen. 
</P>
</TEXT>
