<HEADLINE> King Hussein Paid Condolences to Air Show Victim </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, July 27 (Xinhua) - King Hussein of Jordan here today
paid his last respect to a Jordanian pilot killed Saturday in a
plane crash during an airshow in Belgium.
</P>
<P>
The king expressed his deep condolences to the family members
of Captain Omar Hani Bilal and to his colleagues at the Royal Air
Force and the Royal Falcons Club, Radio Jordan reported.
</P>
<P>
Eight people, including Bilal, were killed and 55 spectators
injured Saturday when Bilal's plane crashed during the performance
by the Jordanian Royal Falcons for an airshow in Ostende, Belgium.
</P>
<P>
Bilal, an experienced pilot, had made numerous outstanding
performance in the past and won some medals for best solo display.
</P>
<P>
A winner of a Hussein Silver Medal for (Carrer) Excellence, he
performed in international airshows in Britain, France, Turkey,
Italy and some other countries.
</P>
<P>
The Royal Falcons team, which represents Jordan in most
international airshow, boasts the best Jordanian pilots,
semi-official Jordan Times reported today. 
</P>
</TEXT>
