<HEADLINE> Jordan, Palestine Discuss Trade Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, July 27 (Xinhua) -- The Jordanian-Palestinian Technical
Committee met here today to put forth a joint mechanism to
facilitate the goods inflows between Jordan and the Palestinian
territories.
</P>
<P>
Both sides were keen to boost trade exchanges, said Jordanian
Minister of Trade, Industry and Supply Hani Mulki, after holding
talks with Hany Salami, an adviser to Palestinian President Yasser
Arafat, Radio Jordan reported.
</P>
<P>
The trade volume between Jordan and the Palestinians reached
21 million U.S. dollars in the first eight months of 1996,
compared to 20 million dollars in the whole year of 1995,
according to official statistics.
</P>
<P>
However, Amman Chamber of Industry Chairman Khaldoun Abu
Hassan was quoted as saying recently that the goods flows were
slower than expected and this could only be attributed to the
Israeli security measures.
</P>
<P>
Israel wanted to continue its monopoly of the Palestinian
market which has no choice but absorbs between 2.7 billion
dollars and 4 billion dollars annually worth of Israeli-made
products, the chairman stressed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
