<HEADLINE> China Bans Poultry Import from Britain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 28 (Xinhua) -- The State Ministry of Agriculture
recently banned the import of poultry and related products from
Britain, and approved imports of sweet cherries from the
Washington State of the United States, kiwi from the North Island
of New Zealand, and bananas from Panama, Ecuador and Costa Rica.
</P>
<P>
Since January this year, about eleven cases of New Town Disease
have been reported in Britain. The virus has spread to four
chicken farms and seven turkey farms there.
</P>
<P>
To protect China's poultry industry and prevent the disease
from spreading to China, the country as of June 18 banned the
imports of poultry and related products from Britain in accordance
with the law on quarantining border-crossing animals and
plants. In addition, all approval lists issued by the State Animal
and Plant Quarantine Bureau are invalid, and all the poultry and
related products should be sent back to Britain or destroyed.
</P>
</TEXT>
