<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China To Be Top Color TV Manufacturer By 2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 28 (Xinhua) -- China will become the world's
leading producer of color TVs by the year 2000, when it is
expected to turn out 33 million sets, eight million of which will
be sold overseas, sources at the State Planning Commission said
today.
</P>
<P>
The country currently has the capacity to manufacture 30
million color TVs annually, with a yearly output of 25 million
sets, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
But some problems have hampered the development of the industry
in China: The country mainly produces low- and middle-level
products, has difficulty developing new products, relies on
imports for some key parts, and moves slowly in exploring the
international market.
</P>
<P>
The commission has proposed that during the Ninth Five-Year
Plan period (1996-2000), the industry should speed up industrial
restructuring by forming more manufacturing company groups. It
should also put a stop to the practice of blindly setting up and
expanding production lines, improve the ability to develop new
products, and do more to open the international market.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the industry should further explore the domestic
rural market, and crackdowns should be made on the smuggling of
color TVs and parts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
