<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> All People Urged To Save Water </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 28 (Xinhua) -- A senior Chinese official today
called on the country to use water economically and to be fully
aware of the urgent need to conserve it.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Premier Jiang Chunyun discussed the issue during today's
national telephone and TV conference on the work of water
conservancy which was jointly held by the State Planning
Commission, the Ministry of Water Conservancy and the Ministry of
Construction.
</P>
<P>
According to Jiang, who is also a member of the Political
Bureau of the Central Committee of the Chinese Communist Party,
China is short of water resources; It's per capita possession of
water resources reaches only one fourth of the world's average.
</P>
<P>
He also pointed out that there is a serious problem of wasting
water in the country as the use rates of water in agricultural and
industrial sectors stand at merely 30-40 percent and 50-60
percent, respectively.
</P>
<P>
To provide more water resources and save water has become a
strategic issue for the country's sustained economic and social
development, he stressed.
</P>
<P>
While trying to find more water resources, greater efforts
should be made to build up water-saving industries and cities, he
said.
</P>
<P>
He suggested that more water conservancy projects be built, and
advanced technology be adopted to reduce the consumption of water
in farming and industries and prevent water sources from being
polluted.
</P>
<P>
Jiang told the conference that the central government has set
up a water conservancy fund to encourage the construction of
water-saving facilities.
</P>
<P>
From now on, he said, the government will not approve projects
that do not meet the requirements for water-conservancy.
</P>
</TEXT>
