<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 28 (Xinhua) -- The sensitive index on the
Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) market today lost 8.33 points to
4,181.48 from last weekend's close of 4189.81.
</P>
<P>
The national index, however, edged up by 1.53 points to
1,824.63 from last Friday's close of 1,823.10.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 and U.S. dollar index increased to 409.15 and
190.34 from last weekend's close of 407.25 and 189.92
respectively.
</P>
<P>
A sharp fall of the share prices of the India Textile Co.(ITC)
led the sensitive index to fall in the stock market today
following heavy squaring up selling in this heavy weighted share
as it came out of no-delivery period last Friday.
</P>
<P>
The day was marked by narrow movements with the BSE sensitive
index moving in a range between 4,163.53 and 4,197.21 before
closing at 4,181.48 today.
</P>
<P>
Brokers said that shares always attract brisk buying when they
enter no-delivery period and was the other way round when they
come out of no-delivery period.  
</P>
