<TEXT>
<P>
PETALING JAYA, Malaysia, July 28 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li
Peng and his Japanese counterpart Ryutaro Hashimoto will exchange
visit this year, according to a Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman
here today.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese prime minister will visit China in early September
while Li Peng will visit Japan within this year with dates yet to
be fixed.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting of the Chinese and Japanese foreign ministers
here today, the two sides expressed the hope that the visits would
further contribute to the healthy and steady development of
bilateral relations, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice Premier and Foreign Minister Qian Qichen said
during the meeting that the 25th anniversary of the normalization
of Sino-Japanese relations should be warmly celebrated.
</P>
<P>
