visits of the two prime ministers would lay a solid foundation for
the development of bilateral relations in the next 25 years.
</P>
<P>
The two foreign ministers also shared the view that the two
sides should speed up the process of negotiations on a new
agreement on fisheries and finalize the accord soon, the spokesman
said.
</P>
<P>
During their meeting, the two foreign ministers also discussed
international and regional issues of common concern including the
U.N. reform and the Korean Peninsula issue.
</P>
<P>
On the U.N. reform, Qian said the reform should reflect the
demands of the developing countries and ensure their
representation.
</P>
<P>
