<HEADLINE> Vaccination Campaign Against Measles Kicks Off in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 28 (Xinhua) -- More than 13,300 Hong Kong
teenagers received measles inoculation here today, the first day
of a vaccination campaign against a predicted measles outbreak
early next year.
</P>
<P>
It is the biggest vaccination campaign ever mounted in Hong
Kong. Dr. Margaret Chan, director of health, estimated that about
1.2 million Hong Kong people, mainly aged between 12 and 19, need
this special vaccination.
</P>
<P>
The first phase of the campaign runs between July 28 and
September 6. Dr. Chan said that response from the local community
has been encouraging.
</P>
<P>
Two weeks before the start of the campaign, more than 290,000
appointment slips had been distributed, accounting for half of the
target population in the first phase.  
