<HEADLINE> Hong Kong's Court of Final Appeal in Operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 28 (Xinhua) -- The Court of Final Appeal (CFA),
the super appellate in the Hong Kong Special Administrative
Region (HKSAR), is ready to accept and hear cases at any time as
of today.
</P>
<P>
Also today, the new appointments of 15 non-permanent judges of
the court took effect. This means the completion of final
formation of the CFA.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong had no power of final adjudication during the 156
years of British rule, which ended at midnight on June 30. In
December 1984, the Chinese and British sides reached agreement
that the HKSAR should have the power of final adjudication.
</P>
<P>
The Basic Law, adopted in April 1990, stipulates that the power
of final adjudication of the HKSAR shall be vested in the Court
of Final Appeal of the HKSAR.
</P>
<P>
In May and June this year, the Provisional Legislative Council
of the HKSAR approved the proposal to appoint Andrew Li as the
Chief Justice of the CFA and Henry Litton, Charles Ching and Kemal
Bokhary as CFA permanent judges. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
