<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Geo-Engineering Group Corporation Founded in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 28 (Xinhua) -- The China Geo-Engineering Group
Corporation (CGEGC), has been established by the Ministry of
Geology and Mineral Resources, it was announced in Beijing today.
</P>
<P>
The ministry set up the new company group, with approval from
the State Economic and Trade Commission, as an important step to
adjust its strategic development structure.
</P>
<P>
With China Geo-Engineering Co. at its core, the company group
is composed of more than 40 domestic and overseas enterprises. It
is a large cross-trade, trans-regional, international business
group mainly engaged in engineering, technology, trade, real
estate, finance and labor export.
</P>
<P>
Participation in international engineering cooperation will be
an important part of the group's efforts to explore the market.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Premier Li Peng sent a message of congratulations for
the establishment of the company group.
</P>
<P>
Zou Jiahua, Vice Premier and also a member of the Political
Bureau of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China
(CPC), unveiled the sign that bears the name of the group
company and also made a speech at a symposium held by CGEGC.
</P>
<P>
Other ministry officials also attended the inauguration of the
company group and discussed development plans together with
members of the CGEGC.
</P>
<P>
At today's symposium, participants suggested that the new
company should focus on project contracting, and vigorously
explore the overseas project contracting market and domestic
construction project market.
</P>
<P>
The company group has set a goal to become one of China's top
50 construction engineering enterprises and will bring in up to
three billion yuan in business volume by the year of 2000.
</P>
<P>
Zheng Qiyu was appointed President of the Board of CGEGC and Ma
Yongyuan as vice-president at today's ceremony. 
</P>
</TEXT>
