<DOCNO> XIE19970728.0051 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong to Launch Retirement Protection Scheme </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 28 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong sets to launch the
Mandatory Provident Fund (MPF) Scheme by the end of 1998, so as to
 provide an enlarged retirement protection umbrella for its aging
population, according to a principal official of the Special
Administrative Region (SAR) government here today.
</P>
<P>
Rafael Hui, secretary for Financial Services, said today, "The
target of the Hong Kong SAR government is to implement the MPF
Scheme as soon as possible." He hoped that most of the preparatory
 work would be completed by the end of next year, and the MPF
system could commence operations soon afterwards.
</P>
<P>
The MPF Scheme is a privately managed, mandatory, fully funded
scheme supervised by the government, according to the official.
</P>
<P>
For a long time, protection for the aged in Hong Kong has been
based on individual savings or insurance arrangements, or on the
publicly managed Comprehensive Social Security Assistance Scheme,
which is financed by tax revenue to offer bottom line support for
the needy.
</P>
<P>
"However, less than one third of the workforce of three million
 people is covered by voluntary retirement scheme," said
Hui. "Prudence demands that we establish a formal retirement
system as soon as possible, involving both employees and
employers."
</P>
<P>
Considering the aging population, he said that a MPF scheme
should be set up as soon as possible. "Otherwise, an intolerable
burden will be put on our taxpayers in future," he added.
</P>
<P>
People aged 65 or above currently accounts for ten percent of
Hong Kong's population of 6.4 million, and the percentage will
rise to 13 percent in 20 years' time and will further move up to
20 percent in another 20 years' time.
</P>
<P>
To implement the retirement protection system, the government
has worked out the MPF draft legislation to solicit comments from
various sectors. The next step is to study in detail these
comments and submit the legislation for enactment as soon as
possible, Hui said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
