<HEADLINE> Renowned Chinese Economist Dies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 28 (Xinhua) -- Chen Daisun, a well-known Chinese
economist and educator, died due to illness this morning in
Beijing. He was 97.
</P>
<P>
Dr. Chen was a professor at Beijing University, member of the
Second and Eighth National Committee of the Chinese People's
Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC), and Standing Committee
member of the sixth and seventh National Committee of the CPPCC.
</P>
<P>
After receiving his Ph.D. from Harvard University in the United
States, Dr. Chen returned to China in 1927 and devoted his life to
higher education in China.
</P>
<P>
He spent 70 years educating professional personnel for the
nation and scored great academic achievements at Qinghua
University, Southwest Union University, and Beijing University.
</P>
<P>
The funeral committee for Dr. Chen is made up of Chinese
leaders, teachers and students. Chen Jia'er, president of Beijing
University, will head the committee.
</P>
<P>
A ceremony for paying last respects to the remains of Dr. Chen
will be held at Beijing Babaoshan Cemetery for Revolutionaries.
</P>
</TEXT>
