<HEADLINE> 29 PKK Rebels Killed in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, July 28 (Xinhua) -- Twenty-nine rebels of the outlawed
Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) were killed in military operations
staged by the Turkish security forces over last week in
southeastern Turkey, an official statement said today.
</P>
<P>
The statement issued by the Emergency Regional Rule said that
three government soldiers and one village guard were also killed
during the armed clashes.
</P>
<P>
The security forces captured four PKK members while five PKK
guerrillas surrendered, it added.
</P>
<P>
In another development, the semi-official Anatolia News Agency
reported today that a group of PKK militants launched an attack on
Kandilli field in Hakkari province bordering Iran and kidnaped
nine villagers who were cutting grass.
</P>
<P>
The news agency added that Turkish security forces have started
operations to free the abducted villagers and capture the PKK
guerrillas.
</P>
<P>
The PKK has been fighting a 13-year-old separatist war for
autonomy, which has claimed over 27,000 lives in eastern and
southeastern Turkey since August 1984. 
</P>
