<HEADLINE> Bell Recast to Recall National Humiliation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, July 28 (Xinhua) -- Students and teachers of Nankai
University in Tianjin gathered here today for the unveiling of the
recast university bell which was bombed by Japanese invaders 60
years ago.
</P>
<P>
On July 28 and 29, 1937, Japanese invaders attacked the campus of
Nankai University. The 6,000 kg university bell, inscribed with
The Diamond Sutra, was destroyed.
</P>
<P>
The students of Nankai University suggested earlier this year
that the bell be recast as a reminder of the national humiliation
and also as a means of patriotism education.
</P>
<P>
The bell is 1.937 meters tall, symbolizing the 1937 Japanese
invasion.
</P>
<P>
University officials said that the bell will be rung for
national days, important commemorative days and commencements.
</P>
