perfect," according to one surveyed passenger on a Hainan
flight. "They are first-rate of all aircrews in China."
</P>
<P>
With 13 airplanes in the company, Hainan Airways shares over 40
percent of the airline market of Hainan Province in south China.
</P>
<P>
"Quality service becomes our lifeline," said Chen Feng,
chairman of Hainan Airways. "We cannot survive without good
service in the increasingly competitive airline market." 
