for economic growth, Fu said. And the African people have a
tradition of loving peace and pursuing progress, he added.
</P>
<P>
China values Africa, Fu noted, and is ready to continue to work
with African countries to build, with an eye toward the 21st
century, a long-term stable relationship between countries that
features cooperation in all aspects.
</P>
<P>
The Sino-African ties are the model of sincere, equal and
friendly cooperative relations between developing countries.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese officer briefed the Nigerian visitors on China's
defensive defense policy and its military construction.
</P>
<P>
Abubakar, also member of Nigeria's Provisional Ruling Council,
said Sani Abacha, Nigeria's head of state and chairman of the
Provisional Ruling Council hopes to know more about China and
hopes the two countries will conduct more cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, Abubakar said, Abacha personally asked him to come
to China. He added his visit is also meant to include further
discussion with China on ways for the two armies to cooperate.
</P>
<P>
Abubakar thanked China for its important contribution to the
liberation cause of Africa and its long-standing help to Nigeria.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the talks, Fu presided over a welcoming ceremony for
Abubakar, who arrived here Sunday at the invitation of Fu. 
</P>
