<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, July 28 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Qinghai Province,
to the northeast of the Tibet Autonomous Region, saw its posts and
telecommunications business rise 39.5 percent to 148 million yuan
during the first half of the year, as compared with the same
months last year.
</P>
<P>
Experts estimate that the province, located more than 3,000
meters above sea level, is likely to witness a second year of
robust business growth rate this year, after earning more than 200
million yuan in 1996.
