<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka Denies Allegations of Shooting Indians </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 28 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka today denied its forces
destroyed an Indian trawler and shot dead two Indian fishermen off
the northern coast of island country, according to a news release
from the Foreign Ministry here.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lankan Foreign Minister Lakshman Kadirgamar told Indian
High Commissioner in Colombo Nareshwar Dayal that a thorough
investigation conducted by the Ministry of Defense proved that
neither the navy nor the air force were involved in the alleged
shooting incidents.
</P>
<P>
On July 16, Indian fishermen complained that the Sri Lankan
navy had shot and destroyed an Indian trawler, killing two Indian
fishermen.
</P>
<P>
On July 17, the Indian high commissioner complained that
another Indian fishing vessel had been attacked by the Sri Lankan
air force.
</P>
<P>
With reference to the July 17 incident, Kadirgamar said the
government of Sri Lanka categorically refutes the monstrous
allegation that Sri Lankan aircraft deliberately intruded deep
into the Indian territorial waters and attacked fishermen off
Arcotthurai on the Indian coast.
</P>
<P>
Kadirgamar told the Indian high commissioner that it must
always be remembered that the Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam
(LTTE) rebels waging a 14-year war for a separate state, are
constantly looking out for opportunities of disrupting the good
relations that exist between Sri Lanka and India.  
</P>
