<HEADLINE> East China Province's Ports See More Business </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, July 28 (Xinhua) -- Ports in east China's Fujian
Province handled more goods during the first half of the year than
in the same period last year, with imports showing a greater
growth rate than that of exports.
</P>
<P>
The ports received 10.355 million tons of goods during the
January-June period, a 60.2 percent rise over last year, which is
a historic achievement, according to the province's customs
officials.
</P>
<P>
The imports skyrocketed by 72.8 percent to 6.753 million tons,
while the exports went up 40.8 percent to 3.6 million tons.
</P>
<P>
Fujian's foreign trade volume rose along with that of the rest
of the country during the half-year period, when China's total
foreign trade volume climbed 13.1 percent to 143.87 billion US
dollars. 
</P>
