<HEADLINE> Iraqi President Accuses US of Politicizing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, July 28 (Xinhua) -- Iraqi President Saddam Hussein
has described the United States as the biggest environment
polluter in the world, accusing it of having been politicizing
the environment issue.
</P>
<P>
The Iraqi president made the accusation during a cabinet
meeting held Sunday evening, the Iraqi New Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
He underlined the necessity of giving attention to what takes
place at international and regional conferences, especially when
Westerners claim that a given branch of industry is
environment-polluting, for they have often abandoned such a
branch of industry and are subsequently attempting to deprive
other nations of engaging in it with the aim of keeping them
backward.
</P>
<P>
The agency said that the cabinet meeting discussed a study of
environmental conditions in Iraq submitted by Iraq's Environment
Protection Council, and took measures to improve environmental
conditions giving special attention to keeping rivers clean.
