<HEADLINE> Canberra Phone Numbers Go to Eight Digits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, July 28 (Xinhua) -- Canberra telephone numbers will
gain one more digit and the area code for the capital of Australia
will be changed on August 18, the Australian Communications
Authority said today.
</P>
<P>
As part of the nationwide renumbering, Canberra numbers will
have a "6" added to the front to become eight-digit numbers and
switch from the "06" to the "02" area code.
</P>
<P>
For 12 months after the change, callers will be able to get
through on the new or old numbers. Then for another three months,
people calling the old number will receive a recorded message
about the change.
</P>
<P>
The renumbering, which will be completed next year, will
increase the capacity from 69 million numbers to about half a
billion numbers while reducing Australia's 54 area codes to four.
</P>
<P>
</P>
