<HEADLINE> China, Thailand See Good Prospects for Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PETALING JAYA, Malaysia, July 28 (Xinhua) -- China and Thailand
said today that there exist good prospects for their cooperation
in the economic, trade, transportation, technological and other
fields.
</P>
<P>
At their meeting here today, Chinese Vice Premier and Foreign
Minister Qian Qichen and Thai Foreign Minister Prachuab Chaiyasarn
said the relations between the two countries have registered
further development since Prime Minister Chavalit Yongchaiyudh
visited China in April this year, a Chinese Foreign Ministry
spokesman told reporters after the meeting.
</P>
<P>
They believed that cooperation of mutual benefit played a
positive role in their respective countries' sustained economic
growth.
</P>
<P>
The two foreign ministers pointed out that both countries
cooperated well in international and regional matters and are
devoted to maintaining peace and stability in their region and
promoting regional economic development and prosperity.
</P>
<P>
They are confident that the two countries will further increase
their coordination and cooperation for this purpose.
</P>
<P>
Qian and Prachuab also exchanged views on the situation in
Cambodia, where fighting broke out on July 5 and 6 between the
forces of Co-Prime Ministers Norodom Ranariddh and Hun Sen,
resulting in the ouster of the former.
</P>
<P>
Qian expressed his appreciation of the effort made by Thailand
and other countries of the Association of Southeast Asian Nations
to help restore stability in Cambodia.
</P>
<P>
Prachuab thanked China for its understanding and impartial
position on the matter.
</P>
<P>
The two ministers are here attending the ASEAN Post Ministerial
Conference. 
