<HEADLINE> HK Sea Traffic Up in First Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 28 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's ocean-going port
traffic grew five percent in the first three months of this year,
while total capacity grew eight percent, according to today's
South China Morning Post.
</P>
<P>
The statistics show 10,404 vessels, with a total capacity of
46.8 million tons, entered the port between January and March,
while 10,411 vessels with a total of 47 million tons departed.
</P>
<P>
Officials estimate that, compared with the same period last
year, inbound cargo increased by three percent to 20.4 million
tons, of which 81 percent were imports and 19 percent
transshipment freight.
</P>
<P>
The amount of exported cargo rose by eight percent to 9.5
million tons compared with the same period last year, of which 56
percent was direct exports and 44 percent was transshipment
cargo.  
</P>
</TEXT>
