<HEADLINE> Officials in Fujian Help School Drop-outs with Donations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, July 28 (Xinhua) -- Government officials in east
China's Fujian Province have donated 1.65 million yuan to help
school drop-outs resume their education.
</P>
<P>
The province has so far received more than 30 million yuan in
donations, and helped 30,000 school drop-outs return to the
classroom, a local education official said.
</P>
<P>
Fujian has also built 108 primary schools with donations,
and provided 200 sets of books for poor pupils, he said.
</P>
<P>
The province has established scholarships for 160 college
students in need of financial aid, and set up a fund to monetarily
reward 100 outstanding primary school teachers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
