<HEADLINE> Nigeria's Cocoa Export Up by 20 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, July 28 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria's cocoa export totalled
167,651 tons in 1996, up by 20 percent over that of 1995, the
Nigerian Tribune reported today.
</P>
<P>
Statistics from the Federal Production Inspection Services
show that Nigeria's cocoa export is also much higher than the
135,000 to 140,000 tons predicted by the International Cocoa
Organization.
</P>
<P>
However, the report said, Nigeria's cocoa export this year is
now threatened by aging plantations and little efforts in
fostering new cultivations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
