<HEADLINE> North China Province's Tourism Prosperous </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, July 28 (Xinhua) -- North China's Shanxi Province
received nearly 40,000 overseas tourists during the first half of
this year, a jump of more than 50 percent over the same period of
last year, according to the provincial tourism bureau.
</P>
<P>
The province earned 11.27 million US dollars through receiving
overseas tourists during this period. Meanwhile, it hosted 10.29
million domestic tourists, earning some two billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Bureau experts say that the sudden upswing in the province's
tourism sector has something to do with improved airway,
expressway and telecommunications facilities, the result of the
province's concentrated efforts in infrastructure construction in
recent years.
</P>
<P>
Shanxi is a yellow-earthed hilly region along the Yellow
River. Though it possesses a wealth of ancient architecture and
other cultural sites, it used to suffer from lackluster tourism
interest because of its poor infrastructure facilities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
