<DOCNO> XIE19970728.0094 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> North China Province Maintains Economic Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, July 28 (Xinhua) -- North China's Hebei Province
had a GDP of 170 billion yuan (about 20.5 billion US dollars) in
the first half of this year, up 14.7 percent from the same period
last year.
</P>
<P>
The agricultural sector saw an increase of 9.2 percent, while
industrial and service sectors rose 14.7 percent and 12.7 percent,
respectively. The province's summer grain harvest was 12.9 billion
kg, up 11.2 percent from the same last year period.
</P>
<P>
Industrial production has increased rapidly. In the first six
months, industrial output totaled 145 billion yuan, representing
an increase of 16.3 percent, and industries' pre-tax profits were
12.6 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Investment in fixed assets totaled 25.7 billion yuan, 22.2
percent higher than the 1996 figure. Spending on agriculture and
the service sector went up 200 percent and 37 percent,
respectively, and in energy and transportation, 62.8 percent and
57 percent, respectively.
</P>
<P>
Retail sales were up 19 percent, and the retail price index is
up 3.1 percentage points, its lowest increase in recent years.
</P>
<P>
Average per capita income in towns and cities was 2,469 yuan,
up 12.6 percent and in rural areas, 949.2 yuan, up 7.3 percent.
</P>
</TEXT>
