<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tehran's Top Officials Arrested for Corruption </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, July 28 (Xinhua) -- Three senior municipal officials in
Tehran were arrested Sunday on charges of corruption as part of
sweeping crackdown on corrupt bureaucrats in Iran, the Persian
daily Iran reported today.
</P>
<P>
The daily, an organ of the Iranian government, said that these
officials are Gholamreza Qobbeh, deputy mayor for administrative
and financial affairs, Nassajiyan Bajian, director-general of the
municipality's security branch, and Morteza Shapouriyan, mayor of
District-5 in western Tehran.
</P>
<P>
The daily added that a number of managers working for
companies affiliated with the municipality have also been arrested.
</P>
<P>
The office of Tehran's Mayor Gholamhossein Karbaschi declined
to comment on the arrests. The public relations office of the
municipality could neither confirm nor reject the reports.
</P>
<P>
However, the public relations office of the justice ministry
said that the ministry is intent on bringing corrupt officials to
justice based on the orders of Iranian Supreme Leader Ali
Khamenei.
</P>
<P>
"We will not allow the rise of a class of people who have
become rich through illegal means," Khamenei told his people two
weeks ago.
</P>
<P>
An unnamed justice ministry official clarified that the records
obtained by the ministry showed that the municipal managers
arrested were involved in squandering public resources.
</P>
<P>
"While searching the premises that belong to them, we found
documents that show they squandered the public treasury," he
said.
</P>
<P>
He said that a dossier is formed in the judicial branches to
investigate the case. "We will inform the public with further
details on this case." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
