<HEADLINE> "Venice of the East" To Hold Silk Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SUZHOU, July 28 (Xinhua) -- East China's city of Suzhou, the
world's largest silk-production base, is to host its sixth silk
festival this autumn to boost both trade and tourism of the silk
industry.
</P>
<P>
The festival, which is to run from September 20 to 25, will
feature a foreign trade fair, exhibitions and sales
promotions. The city aims to show its economic achievements over
the past few years during the event.
</P>
<P>
Festival participants will have opportunities to attend several
large-scale evening parties and public activities.
</P>
<P>
Sources said that 2,000-plus overseas business people and
sister-city representatives will attend.
</P>
<P>
The city, known as the "Venice of the East," has more than
7,000 overseas-backed firms with a total of 10 billion US
dollars-worth of investments. More than 160 world-famous
transnational corporations and consortiums have investments here.
</P>
</TEXT>
