<HEADLINE> Share Prices Fall Back on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, July 28 (Xinhua) -- Share prices fell back on the
Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times Industrials Index
declined by 5.95 points to close at 1,975.01 points today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume stood at 163.64 million units, valued
at 463.07 million Singapore dollars (about 317.17 million US
dollars). Declines outnumbered advances by 218 to 110, while 282
other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The Keppel Corporation was the most actively traded stock as it
registered a turnover of 8.36 million units. It was followed by
Asia Food Properties which had 6.44 million shares traded. Gul
Tech was next with 6.33 million shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
Venture warrant9907 led the gainers of the day as it rose by 45
cents to finish at 6.1 Singapore dollars. KepFELS gained 23 cents
to end at 5.15 Singapore dollars, while the United Overseas Bank
(UOB) Foreign closed 20 cents higher at 16.5 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, local property developer City Developments was
the biggest loser as it declined by 80 cents to end at 13.1
Singapore dollars. GE Life fell by 70 cents to close at 18.3
Singapore dollars. And local computer sound card maker Creative 50
finished 60 cents lower at 33.9 Singapore dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
