<HEADLINE> China, South Korea Pledge to Boost Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PETALING JAYA, Malaysia, July 28 (Xinhua) -- China and South
Korea today pledged to make joint efforts to further promote their
cooperation in various areas.
</P>
<P>
At a meeting here today, Chinese Vice Premier and Foreign
Minister Qian Qichen and South Korean Foreign Minister Yoo
Chong-ha highly commended the development of the relations between
their two countries since the establishment of diplomatic ties
five years ago.
</P>
<P>
Yoo once again congratulated China on its resumption of
exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong on July 1 this year and
expressed the conviction that after Hong Kong's return to China,
South Korea's economic and trade ties with both China's inland
areas and Hong Kong will further grow.
</P>
<P>
Qian pointed out that the Chinese government is following the
principles of "one country, two systems," "Hong Kong people
governing Hong Kong" with a high degree of autonomy.
</P>
<P>
"Hong Kong will maintain long-term prosperity and stability and
the legitimate economic and trade interests of various countries
there will be protected," he declared.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the economic and trade relations between various
countries and Hong Kong will surely further increase, he said.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the quadripartite talks on the Korean Peninsula,
the Chinese foreign minister pointed out that his country has
always worked for peace and stability on the peninsula.
</P>
<P>
"We believe that the main task of the quadripartite talks is to
set up a mechanism for peace on the peninsula and such a mechanism
is of great importance for maintaining peace and stability there,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that the relations between the parties
concerned will continuously improve.
</P>
<P>
Qian also expressed China's readiness to play its role in
making the talks fruitful and in establishing a mechanism for
peace on the peninsula as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
The two ministers are here attending the ASEAN Post Ministerial
Conference here. 
</P>
</TEXT>
