<HEADLINE> Pond Fishing Farms to Help Diversify Uganda's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, July 28 (Xinhua) -- Over 50 fish ponds have been dug
in Mityana, central Mubende district in Uganda as part of the
government's effort to diversify the country's farming
activities, a local paper reported today.
</P>
<P>
A Kampala-based daily, The New Vision, said in a report that
the ponds were dug with the help from Actionaid, a British
non-government organization.
</P>
<P>
Starting its work in the area in 1982, the NGO provides with
farming materials, and construction materials for road repairing
and advices in farming technology to needy families to encourage
them to go to market.
</P>
<P>
Most fish products are to be consumed by local farmers, but
some of them are to be sold on markets, the report said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
