<HEADLINE> ROK Food Processor Enters Chinese Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 28 (Xinhua) -- The Cheiljedang (CJ) Group, a
major food processor from the Republic of Korea (ROK), recently
invested 200 million yuan to establish three enterprises in China.
</P>
<P>
The CJ Group and Beijing Changning Group established the
Beijing CJ Changning Food Company Ltd. with an investment of 115
million yuan. The new venture will produce over 30,000 tons of
different soft drinks annually.
</P>
<P>
The ROK group also invested 7.5 million yuan in the
solely-funded CJ Ulan Flour Company Ltd., and 70 million yuan in a
Qingdao meat processing plant.
</P>
<P>
CJ currently exports products to some 60 countries and has an
annual sales volume of over 2 billion US dollars. The group
produces a variety of products for the chemical, pharmaceutical
and service industries.
</P>
<P>
The group expects its 1997 sales in China to hit 300 million
yuan, with the figure expected to rise to well over two billion
yuan annually along with an expanded scale of production an entry
into new sectors. CJ fully expects to become one of China's
largest comprehensive food processing enterprises. 
</P>
