long as they are good for our city," he said.
</P>
<P>
Mulenga said the vendors have been let to take over the
streets making it very difficult for shop owners to do business
and that all parking lots have also been turned into "shops".
</P>
<P>
Vendors must operate their business hundred meters away from
shopping centers, he noted.
</P>
<P>
If the situation is not redressed in the shortest possible
time, Lusaka will remain the dirtiest city in the region, he
warned.
</P>
<P>
The city council, vendors desk at the State House and his
office will soon meet to resolve the matter, he said. 
