<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hot Weather in South Korea Causes Accidents, Deaths </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, July 28 (Xinhua) -- The heat wave, which has encompassed
South Korea for about a week, has caused various heat-related
accidents and deaths.
</P>
<P>
Sunstroke caused several deaths. On July 24, a 22-year-old
military trainee suddenly collapsed and died during a training
exercise. In an other case, a man collapsed on his way home after
a several-hour work on a construction site.
</P>
<P>
About 10 people have died from heart failure after the shock
from suddenly entering cold water.
</P>
<P>
Power supplies were suspended for hours in Seoul and other
cities due to excessive use of electricity, leaving some people
trapped in elevators and fans and air conditioners out of
operation.
</P>
<P>
Under the heat wave, a car in a ground parking lot in Seoul was
partially destroyed on July 26 by fire caused by an overheated
engine after a two-hour use of the air conditioner in the car.
</P>
<P>
Another four or five cases of fires in cars were caused by
explosions of disposable gas lighters left in the car. 
</P>
</TEXT>
