<HEADLINE> China Increases Paper Plate Production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 28 (Xinhua) -- Quzhou Green Dinner Sets Co. Ltd.
recently opened a paper plate production line in Quzhou, east
China's Zhejiang Province, according to a recent issue of the
China Environmental News.
</P>
<P>
The new line has increased the company's daily capacity by
five-fold to 500,000 durable, oil resistant and waterproof dinner
sets, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
The company's expanded production of paper plates will help to
solve environmental problems resulting from so-called "white
pollution" created by the widespread use of plastic boxes.
</P>
<P>
The Quzhou company recently signed a contract to supply 150
million paper dinner sets to the Guangzhou Railway Bureau on an
annual basis.
</P>
<P>
Recent statistics show that China's fast-food industry uses
well over 10 billion throwaway styrofoam fast food containers
annually. In July this year, the Ministry of Railways issued a
regulation prohibiting the use of plastic fast-food boxes.
</P>
<P>
Completion of a planned second phase project, scheduled for
next year, will enable the company to reduce costs and raise its
daily production capacity to one million units.
</P>
<P>
Overseas investment continues to flow into the sector, with
joint ventures paper plate production plants currently under
construction in Xi'an and Xiamen.  
</P>
</TEXT>
