<HEADLINE> Egypt, China to Set up Giant Cement Factory in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, July 28 (Xinhua) -- Egypt and China have agreed to
establish a cement factory with an annual production of 1.3
million tonnes in north Sinai peninsula, which will be their
largest industrial joint project.
</P>
<P>
China National Transport Machinery Import and Export Company
(CMC) and Sinai Cement Company signed the 98-million-U.S.-dollar
contract here Sunday on establishing the Sinai Cement Factory.
</P>
<P>
Under the deal, Egypt will purchase from the CMC two sets of
production machinery, each with a capacity of producing 2,000
tonnes of cement a day. China will take charge of the construction
of the factory and provide expertise in production and management.
</P>
<P>
The factory, to be located near Arish, 320 kilometers north of
Cairo, will be put into operation in 34 months, according to the
contract.
</P>
<P>
The late night signing ceremony was attended by more than 200
government officials and businessmen, including Egyptian ministers
of electricity, finance and rural development, as well as Chinese
diplomats. 
</P>
</TEXT>
