<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Women Enjoy Rising Status in Southeast China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, July 28 (Xinhua) -- A recent survey in Fujian Province,
southeast China, revealed that an increasing number of married
couples are sharing decision-making responsibilities.
</P>
<P>
According to the survey, 71.9 percent of responding couples
jointly managed family income, 73.3 percent reporting joint
decision for housing, 71.1 percent for purchases of expensive
items and 68.4 percent for investment and loans.
</P>
<P>
The survey also revealed that 40.8 percent of respondents
shared housework responsibilities.
</P>
<P>
The Provincial Women's Federation recorded an 81.1 percent
response rate for the 3,000 questionnaire survey conducted between
April and May this year.
</P>
<P>
Some 70.4 percent of families considered the gender of a child
to be irrelevant despite China's one child family planning policy,
with 98.5 percent of respondents citing the equal education rights
of male and female children.
</P>
<P>
Spousal equality plays an important role in maintaining
stability and harmony within a family, with 74.4 percent
respondents indicating a harmonious family life. Some 80.2 percent
cited satisfaction with their spouses, with 53.9 percent
indicating a concession attitude and 27 percent solving
problems through discussion.  
</P>
</TEXT>
