<HEADLINE> Township Enterprises Growing up in East China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, July 28 (Xinhua) -- Cottage industries that are part
of China's township enterprise sector in Zhejiang Province, east
China, are rapidly becoming large groups competing profitably
both in China and overseas.
</P>
<P>
The province is the cradle of China's township enterprise
system and has 160 of the country's 1,000 top township
enterprises. In 1992, it began to improve its township enterprise
system, which was characterized by small-scale, loosely-organized
operations that lagged behind in technology.
</P>
<P>
It has more than 150 groups made up of 900,000 township
enterprises, 237 of which have over 100 million yuan in annual
sales and 10 million yuan in profits, and 618 that have joined
China's large and medium-sized township enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Haining city, which is known as the birthplace of China's
leather industry, has turned its helter-skelter leather factories
into large groups that now produce some name-brand goods like
Xuebao (Snow Leopard). Five of the groups do more than 150 million
yuan each in business annually.
</P>
<P>
Shaoxing County is another example. It spent 4.4 billion yuan
last year on technological improvement projects for the textile
industry, adding 11,000 more modern looms. Some of its businesses
like the Asia-Pacific Group have grown to more than a billion yuan
in annual sales, at a time when the rest of China's textile
industry is going downhill.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
