<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 12 Killed in Train Collision near India's Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 28 (Xinhua)-- At least 12 people were killed
and 82 others injured, 22 of them seriously, when a speeding train
rammed into a stationary one near the Capital New Delhi late
Sunday night, Press Trust of India (PTI) said here today.
</P>
<P>
The toll is expected to go up as rescuers struggled to
extricate bodies and survivors in the pre-dawn hours here today,
cutting through the mangled metal coaches which were thrown off
the railway track upon collision.
</P>
<P>
Central Railway spokesman Rakesh Saxena put the toll at eight
killed and 42 injured.
</P>
<P>
The mishap occurred when the Delhi-bound Karnataka Express from
Bangalore, capital of Karnataka state, running 12 hours behind
schedule, overshot a signal and hit the Himsagar Express coming
from Kanyakumari from the rear at full speed at around 23:15 local
time Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The entire rail traffic on the route has been disrupted and a
number of trains have been rescheduled or diverted. The train
traffic is likely to be restored tonight, PTI quoted railway
sources as saying.
</P>
<P>
An inquiry has been ordered into the incident. Preliminary
reports indicated that the Karnataka Express overshot the signal
and hit the stationary Himsagar Express, Divisional Railway
manager K.K.Gupta said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
