<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dialogue Between ASEAN, Partners Called Important </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PETALING JAYA, Malaysia, July 28 (Xinhua) -- The Association of
Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) today called its conferences with
dialogue partners "an important event" in ASEAN's external
relations.
</P>
<P>
"It has provided the ASEAN with opportunities to promote its
interest and engage in exchange of views with the participation of
major players in the region as well as those outside the region,"
Malaysian Foreign Minister Abdullah Ahmad Badawi said here this
morning when he opened the two-day dialogue.
</P>
<P>
Badawi, who is also chairman of the dialogue, known as the
ASEAN Post Ministerial Conference (PMC), noted that ASEAN's
solidarity will be tested with new and more difficult issues, some
of the old issues could resurface in new forms and the rapid
growth of information technology adds another dimension to the
challenges faced by developing countries like those in ASEAN.
</P>
<P>
"To remain viable, the PMC must keep up with these new
demands," Badawi declared.
</P>
<P>
Regional cooperation and international political and economic
issues are expected to be discussed at the conference attended by
ministers of the nine ASEAN member countries -- Brunei, Indonesia,
Laos, Malaysia, Myanmar, the Philippines, Singapore, Thailand and
Vietnam -- and those from the 10 ASEAN dialogue partners --
Australia, Canada, China, India, Japan, South Korea, New Zealand,
Russia, the United States and the European Union.
</P>
<P>
On Cambodia, Badawi said the country "should be given time and
support to resolve its problems."
</P>
<P>
Cambodia was supposed to be admitted into the ASEAN earlier
this month together with Laos and Myanmar. However, its accession
was deferred because of the fighting between the forces of
Co-Prime Ministers Norodom Ranariddh and Hun Sen on July 5 and 6.
</P>
<P>
"A durable and enduring solution to the complex Cambodian
situation must include a heavy percentage of local content,"
Badawi said. "In other words, the Cambodians themselves cannot
avoid taking the necessary steps to solve their problems which are
basically home-grown."
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that the admission of Laos and Myanmar into
ASEAN has further consolidated Southeast Asia as a "cohesive
regional community" as it enters the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
"The success of the ASEAN over the last three decades in
bringing the member countries closer together has strengthened my
belief that mutual understanding and dialogue is the key to peace
and stability in the region," he said.
</P>
<P>
The Malaysian foreign minister added that the ASEAN Regional
Forum, which met here Sunday for the fourth time since it was
started four years ago, has further helped encourage the habit of
consultation and cooperation in the area of security for the
Asia-Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
After a closed-door session this morning, the ASEAN countries
will start holding separate dialogues with each dialogue partner
this afternoon and tomorrow.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
