<HEADLINE> More New Businesses Register in Thailand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, July 28 (Xinhua) -- The number of new businesses
registered in Thailand rose by 11.85 percent in the first half of
this year compared with the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
However, about 91 percent of the newly registered businesses
were small, with capital under 5 million baht (200,000 U.S.
dollars), and 9 percent were capitalized at 5 to 10 million baht
(200,000 to 400,000 dollars) or more.
</P>
<P>
Most of the new firms are in the provinces, where the number
rose by 61 percent, while in and around the capital Bangkok, the
number dropped by 14.15 percent.
</P>
<P>
Most of the newcomers are wholesale and retail businesses,
restaurants and hotels.  
</P>
