<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Earthquake Jolts South Yellow Sea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 28 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 5.1 on
Richter scale jolted China's south Yellow Sea area at 02:31
(Beijing Time) early today.
</P>
<P>
The State Seismological Bureau said the epicenter of the quake
was located in 33.7 degrees north latitude and 122.2 degrees east
longitude.
</P>
<P>
The bureau said the 1997 national conference on earthquake
tendency held earlier had predicted that an earthquake measuring 5
to 6 degrees on Richter scale might hit the area ranging from
Jiangsu-Shandong bordering area and south Yellow Sea.
</P>
<P>
Preliminary reports said residents in Jiangsu Province's
Nantong, Rudong, Zhangjiagang and Changshu cities felt the quake
and some Shanghai citizens also felt the quake.  
</P>
</TEXT>
