<HEADLINE> Bulgarian President to Visit Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Bulgarian President Peter Stoyanov
will pay a state visit to Turkey on July 28 at the invitation of
his Turkish counterpart Suleyman Demirel.
</P>
<P>
At the summit, the two leaders are expected to review a wide
range of regional and international issues and to sign agreements
on cooperation in defense and environment protection.
</P>
<P>
In an exclusive interview with the Bulgarian newspaper "Trud,"
Turkish President Demirel voiced his satisfaction over the rapid
development of Bulgarian-Turkish relations in recent years.
</P>
<P>
"The Turkish-Bulgarian ties reached a really very good level,"
Demirel was quoted as saying before Stoyanov's arrival.
</P>
<P>
"Both countries are showing good will to promote them further
and adopt an identical policy in search for peace and stability in
the region," he told the newspaper, the biggest in Bulgaria.
</P>
<P>
In 1992, the two countries signed a friendship treaty to end
their tension that began with Bulgaria's assimilation campaign
against the Bulgarian ethnic Turks in the Cold War era.
</P>
<P>
Recently, the Turkish government has expressed its support for
Bulgaria's bid to enter the North Atlantic Treaty Organization
(NATO) and to integrate with the European Union (EU). 
</P>
</TEXT>
