<HEADLINE> Colombia Wins Four-nation International Soccer Tourney </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Colombia's Atletico Junior
captured the title after scoring a 2-0 win over Germany's Borussia
Monchengladbach in the Reebok Cup international soccer tournament
in Chicago on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Deyler Sacramento and Hector Mendez collected the two goals for
the Atletico Junior, who finished with a unbeaten record of one
win and one draw.
</P>
<P>
Atletico goalkeeper Jose Pazo made four saves in the shutout at
Soldier Field, one of the sites for the 1994 World Cup tournament.
</P>
<P>
Sacramento scored in the 39th minute to give the Atletico
Junior a 1-0 halftime lead. Mendez added the second goal on a pass
from Ronald Valderrama in the 77th minute.
</P>
<P>
In the only other match on Sunday, Mexico's Necaxa defeat
Brazil's Palmeiras 4-1.
</P>
<P>
Jose Luis Montes de Oca opened the score for Necaxa when he
knocked home a rebound of a Cuauhtemoc Blanco shot. Alex Aguinaga
then scored on a free kick from some 20 meters out over the
Palmeiras wall.
</P>
<P>
Blanco contributed the final two goals for Necaxa.
</P>
<P>
Blanco was named the tournament MVP with three goals, including
one in Necaxa's loss to Monchengladbach in the open game of the
four-nation event. 
</P>
</TEXT>
