<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bank of China Plans Improvements </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 28 (Xinhua) -- The Bank of China, the nation's
leading foreign exchange bank, will try harder to hedge against
financial risks and improve its credit assets in the coming
months.
</P>
<P>
The bank will strive to reduce non-performing loans by two to
three percentage points this year, and to cut the amount of poor
assets in the coming years, BOC President Wang Xuebin said
yesterday in Beijing, today's China Daily reported.
</P>
<P>
Supervision and examination will be strengthened and the
reduction of poor assets will become an important standard to
judge the performance of branches, Wang said during the bank's
national work conference for branch presidents.
</P>
<P>
He also pointed out that clearing bad assets should coincide
with the business expansion.
</P>
<P>
"We will promote the readjustment of assets structure through
business development," he said.
</P>
<P>
Funds will be concentrated to meet the demands of key customers
and projects, he added.
</P>
<P>
And to ensure the continuous expansion of the bank's strength,
the bank will make greater efforts to attract deposits in the
coming months.
</P>
<P>
The bank's outstanding renminbi deposits by the end of June
amounted to 519 billion yuan (62.5 billion US dollars), 30 billion
yuan (3.6 billion US dollars) more than at the end of last year.
</P>
<P>
Its outstanding foreign exchange savings hit 31.4 billion US
dollars, still the lion's share of the nation's total. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
