<HEADLINE> Hingis Wins Her Eighth Title of the Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Top seed Martina Hingis of
Switzerland gained her eighth WTA Tour title this year with an
easy victory of 6-0, 6-2 over six-seeded Conchita Martinez in the
final of the Bank of the West Classic on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Hingis needed just 53 minutes to storm past Martinez and
rewrite her overall record this year to 53-1, including a 30-0
mark on hardcourts.
</P>
<P>
The 16-year-old Hingis, who last month became the youngest
Wimbledon winner this century, also has won the Australian Open,
the Sydney International, Pan Pacific Open, Open Gaz de France,
the Lipton Championships and the Family Circle Cup.
</P>
<P>
Her only loss this year came to Iva Majoli in the final of the
French Open.
</P>
<P>
Hingis was appearing in her ninth WTA Tour final in as many
events this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
