<HEADLINE> Egypt Tops Arab Games Medal Table </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Egypt finished clear winner with 97
gold medals at the eighth Arab Games which ended here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
But Egypt also won the contest for most failed drug tests as
five of its gold winning athletes tested positive for drugs.
</P>
<P>
The five athletes are two wrestlers, a taekwando fighter, a
boxer and volleyball player.
</P>
<P>
Their gold medals were suspended and may be canceled after a
final ruling by the games organising committee later this week.
</P>
<P>
Egypt's dominance at the 15-day games was overwhelming,
especially in wrestling, weightlifting and swimming where the
Egyptian athletes won a total of 65 gold medals.
</P>
<P>
Egypt also took 58 silver and 39 bronze medals for a total of
194 medals. The number is the highest by any conutry at the Arab
Games since 1953.
</P>
<P>
Algeria finished second with 43 golds, 44 silvers and 47 bronze
while Morocco came third with 19 golds, 13 silvers and 17 bronzes.
</P>
<P>
On the final day of the games, games officials announced more
drug violations, rasing the number of athletes who have failed the
dope tests to 12.
</P>
<P>
It is the first time that doping test was held in Arab Games
since the games were first held in 1953. 
</P>
</TEXT>
