<HEADLINE> Egypt Beats Ethiopia in African Nations Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Egypt trounced Ethiopia 8-1 in a
group three qualifier at the African Nations Cup at Alexandria, on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The host team dominated the match from the very beginning with
Hady Khashaba scoring in the first minute. Hashem Hanefi added a
goal four minutes later to make it 2-0 for Egypt.
</P>
<P>
Hazem Imam then scored a hat-trick at the 19th, 36th and 44th
minutes.
</P>
<P>
In the second half, the Egyptian team score three more goals
while Ethiopia's STio Elias scored his country's sole goal in the
60th minute.
</P>
<P>
Earlier on Sunday, Morocco beat Senegal 3-0 in another group
three match.
</P>
<P>
Top two finishers of each group qualify for next year's African
Nations Cup finals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
